
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to add a new node to an existing session node. The [add] slot is used to append a child node to the [.session] node, where the new node contains a [.role] with the value "system" and a [content] node whose value is dynamically retrieved from the [.arguments] node using a lambda expression. The [content] node's value is set to the value of the [system_message] node within [.arguments].
add:x:@.session
   .
      .
         role:system
         content:x:@.arguments/*/system_message
